snippet.textDisplay:
Felt it to the core my being...
Deeply. The following poured out...

“Feeling forced to walk around wearing smile covered masks
No one knows what’s going on inside, no one cares no one asks
So it’s swallowed and hidden, buried deep within my soul
Boiling over, this pressure cooker within is about to explode
So low, feeling so down, but I fear the judgment of pointing fingers
Can’t let my kids see me struggling either, they need a strong father figure
So I’m all alone, all by myself, creating my own internal hell
But to the world everything is okay, I can’t show them all how I really feel” - KATALYST

snippet.textDisplay: In tears listening to this.. My family fell apart at a young age after my parents divorce, and going into my adulthood I still struggle with depression and feel like I have nothing because of it, and it always makes me feel like nobody cares and I'm truly all alone.. I haven't been truly happy since everyone went their separate ways and this was over ten years ago (I'm 19 now) but I can't seem to find a way to get over it and every single day I want to just give up because there's no way of going back to that point in my life, but I know there's nothing I can do and I just do my best to hold on, even when there's nothing left to hold onto. One day at a time. It was a long comment, but if anyone made it this far and feels the same way and don't have anyone to talk to feel free to comment and I'll try to do my best to be here for all that needs someone and always do your best to keep yourself going and never give up
snippet.textOriginal: In tears listening to this.. My family fell apart at a young age after my parents divorce, and going into my adulthood I still struggle with depression and feel like I have nothing because of it, and it always makes me feel like nobody cares and I'm truly all alone.. I haven't been truly happy since everyone went their separate ways and this was over ten years ago (I'm 19 now) but I can't seem to find a way to get over it and every single day I want to just give up because there's no way of going back to that point in my life, but I know there's nothing I can do and I just do my best to hold on, even when there's nothing left to hold onto. One day at a time. It was a long comment, but if anyone made it this far and feels the same way and don't have anyone to talk to feel free to comment and I'll try to do my best to be here for all that needs someone and always do your best to keep yourself going and never give up

snippet.textDisplay:
This line hits the hardest for me..."But in my mind I wish that I could rewind. Press pause and live my life inside a moment in time".

That's the hardest part when you're grieving is getting past the fact that you're never going to see them again... and you just BEG TO GOD to give you one more moment.... see them smile one more time... hear their voice and tell them you love them and just stay in that moment.

I wake up and don't see my shadow. Gonna be cold, until I'm my BPM drops like my life is about to climb with these gangster beatings. I give myself mold.
